  "texts": [
    "A reference to the harmonized standard is then published in the Official Journal of the European Union.",
    "Systems complying with such standards will be (rebuttably) assumed to also comply with the related requirements of the AI Act.",
    "Should this strategy fail, i.e., no harmonized standards be passed, the Act attributes a backup role to the Commission in Article 41.",
    "In this case, the Commission can become active and adopt \"common specifications\".",
    "The AI Act treats technical specifications as the central way of determining compliance with the requirements."
